     <li>
      <font color="#000000">
       <strong>
        Learning Is a Complex and Active Process That Occurs Throughout the Life Span, New Report Says
       </strong>
       <br/>
       (The National Academies of Sciences, Engineering, and Medicine News, 10/4/18)
       <br/>
       A new report from the National Academies of Sciences, Engineering, and Medicine highlights the dynamic process of learning throughout the life span. The report, entitled How People Learn II, also identifies areas in which more research is needed to have an even deeper understanding of human learning. TDLC investigator Dr. Zewelanji Serpell participated on the report committee.
       <a href="http://www8.nationalacademies.org/onpinews/newsitem.aspx?RecordID=24783">
        Read more
       </a>
       <img alt="" border="0" height="16" src="../images/bullet3.gif" width="15"/>
      </font>
     </li>
